  "title": "Pearlstone Block",
  "summaries": [
    "<b>Pearlstone</b> is a <linked>Hardmode</linked> <linked>block</linked> type found in <linked>The Hallow</linked>. It requires at least a <linked>Nightmare Pickaxe</linked>, <linked>Deathbringer Pickaxe</linked>, or <linked>explosives</linked> to mine.",
    "Pearlstone is the Hallow version of <linked>Stone</linked> (similar to <linked>Ebonstone</linked> in <linked>The Corruption</linked>, or <linked>Crimstone</linked> in <linked>The Crimson</linked>). In a way similar to Ebonstone and Crimstone, Pearlstone can be converted into ordinary Stone via <linked>Vile Powder</linked>, <linked>Vicious Powder</linked>, or the <linked>Clentaminator</linked> with the <linked>Green Solution</linked>.",
    "During the initial creation of the Hallow biome upon the defeat of the <linked>Wall of Flesh</linked>, Stone blocks in the conversion path become Pearlstone blocks (see <linked>Hardmode</linked>). Pearlstone itself also continues to spread Hallow to all Stone, <linked>Sand</linked>, <linked>Ice</linked>, and <linked>Grass</linked> covered dirt within a three tile radius. Over time, it will grow Crystal Shards if it is in the Underground or below."
  ],
